A natural person may apply to the Managing Director for registration as a registered verifier ifhe -
* is a resident in Papua New Guinea or elsewhere; and
* meets the verifier accreditation criteria and requirements under the UNFCCC; and
* has -
	* provided sufficient evidence that he has taken out professional indemnity insurance, in the amount prescribed by the Board, with an independent reputable insurance company; and
	* complied with the provisions of the
	* 1978;
	* 1978;
 and
	* registered as a tax payer and is issued with a current certificate of compliance by the Internal Revenue Commission as required by the
	* 1959;
	* 1959;
 and
	* registered a business name under the
	* 2014;
	* 2014;
 and
	* paid an application or registration fee approved by the Board from time to time; and
	* possesses qualifications appropriate to conduct verification.
